eriences, and exploring ways to balance visitor participation and museum curation. The book reports on a three-year cross-disciplinary research project in which artists, design researchers and museum professionals have collaborated to create technology-mediated experiences that merge with the museum environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aArchiving, Conservation and Digitization. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aGame Studies. 4aHeritage Studies. 4aInternet and digital media: arts and performance. 4aLibrary and information sciences / Museology. 4aMedia Studies. 4aMedia studies. 4aScience and Technology. 7aART / Museum Studies.2bisacsh  aHybrid Design, Museums, User Experience, Human-Computer Interaction (HCI), Gifting.1 aBack, Jon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBacon, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenford, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBodiaj, Edgar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCameron, Harriet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDarzentas, Dimitri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEklund, Lina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHviid Mortensen, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLøvlie, Anders, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMalde, Sejul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartindale, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://i